{"type":"message","id":"54bc750a","parentId":"bd769754","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:57:45.005Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r9t2twbywzek_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5106\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 045714 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"lucky-shore","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5106\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 045714 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342665002}}
{"type":"message","id":"861a2f10","parentId":"54bc750a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:57:45.007Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r9t2twbywzek_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 045515\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: TIC (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and the pending TIC experiment task.\r\n\r\nThe key pending action is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to create a concrete action that advances the TIC experiment. Let me first look at what pulse logs exist and understand their structure.\r\n\r\nLet me check the logs directory structure and recent pulse files.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires classifying pulse content as invariant (persistent patterns) vs variant (unique to specific pulse). I need to first examine existing pulse logs to understand their structure and extract features for classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs from `logs/` directory\r\n2. Extracts key entities, insights, and actions from each pulse\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant (repeated across pulses) or variant (unique)\r\n4. Tests prediction of next pulse content based on invariants\r\n5. Outputs accuracy metrics against success criteria\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n$logsDir = \"logs\"\r\n$recentLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $logsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First 20\r\n\r\nif ($recentLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[TIC] Insufficient pulse logs for experiment\"\r\n    exit 0\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract features from each pulse\r\nfunction Extract-Features($content) {\r\n    $features = @{\r\n        Entities = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract entities (lines starting with ## or -)\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ($line -match \"^- \\[ \\]\") { $features.Actions += $line }\r\n        elseif ($line -match \"^## \") { $features.Insights += $line }\r\n        elseif ($line -match \"^-\") { $features.Entities += $line }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build corpus of all features\r\n$allFeatures = @{}\r\nforeach ($log in $recentLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $features = Extract-Features $content\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($entity in $features.Entities) {\r\n        $hash = $entity.GetHashCode()\r\n        if (-not $allFeatures.ContainsKey($hash)) {\r\n            $allFeatures[$hash] = @{\r\n                Text = $entity\r\n                Count = 0\r\n                FirstSeen = $log.LastWriteTime\r\n                LastSeen = $log.LastWriteTime\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        $allFeatures[$hash].Count++\r\n        $allFeatures[$hash].LastSeen = $log.LastWriteTime\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify: invariant if seen in >= 3 pulses, variant if < 3\r\n$invariant = @()\r\n$variant = @()\r\n$total = $allFeatures.Count\r\n\r\nforeach ($key in $allFeatures.Keys) {\r\n    $feat = $allFeatures[$key]\r\n    if ($feat.Count -ge 3) {\r\n        $invariant += $feat.Text\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variant += $feat.Text\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$invariantRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { $invariant.Count / $total } else { 0 }\r\n$variantRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { $variant.Count / $total } else { 0 }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment Results ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Total features: $total\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariant (seen >= 3 pulses): $($invariant.Count) ($([math]::Round($invariantRatio*100,1))%)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Variant (seen < 3 pulses): $($variant.Count) ($([math]::Round($variantRatio*100,1))%)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Prediction Test ===\"\r\n\r\n# Test: predict next pulse contains invariants from previous pulses\r\n$prediction = @()\r\n$actual = @{}\r\n\r\n# Use first 15 pulses to predict 16th\r\n$trainLogs = $recentLogs | Select-Object -First 15\r\n$testLog = $recentLogs | Select-Object -First 1  # Most recent\r\n\r\nif ($testLog) {\r\n    $testContent = Get-Content $testLog.FullName -Raw\r\n    $testFeatures = Extract-Features $testContent\r\n    \r\n    # Predict: any invariant from training should appear in test\r\n    $correct = 0\r\n    $totalPredict = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($inv in $invariant) {\r\n        $totalPredict++\r\n        if ($testContent -match [regex]::Escape($inv.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(20, $inv.Length)))) {\r\n            $correct++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $predictionAccuracy = if ($totalPredict -gt 0) { $correct / $totalPredict } else { 0 }\r\n    Write-Host \"Prediction accuracy: $([math]::Round($predictionAccuracy*100,1))%\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Success Criteria ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariant/Variant Classification: $(if ($invariantRatio -ge 0.7) { 'PASS' } else { 'FAIL' }) (>70% target)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Next-Pulse Prediction: $(if ($predictionAccuracy -ge 0.6) { 'PASS' } else { 'FAIL' }) (>60% target)\"\r\n\r\n# Save results\r\n$results =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:55:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342665005}}
